Preheat the oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Chop the @potatoes{3} lengthways into 1cm slices, then into 1cm wide chips
(no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large (lined) #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}
then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

== Buttered Leeks ==

Trim the @leek{1/2}. Halve lengthways. Thinly slice half widthways (double for
4p).

Place a #pan over medium heat with a knob of @butter{to taste} and a drizzle of
@oil{to taste}.

Once hot, add the sliced leek and season with @salt{to taste} and
@pepper{to taste}.

Cook until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Once softened, remove from the pan and set aside.

== Burgers ==

In a large #bowl, combine the @Worcester Sauce{1%sachet}, @mustard{1%sachet}
and @breadcrumbs{1%pack}.

Add @water{2%tsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp} (double both for 4p).

Add the @Irish Beef Mince{250%grams}, season with @pepper{to taste} and mix
everything together with your hands.

Roll into evenly-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers—1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

> TIP: The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the burgers until browned on the outside and cooked through,
~{10-12%minutes}. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes} and adjust heat if needed.

Once cooked, remove the pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: Burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Place some @grated cheese{50%grams} on top of each burger.

Cover the pan and set aside (off the heat) until the cheese melts,
~{3-4%minutes}.

== Assembly ==

While the burgers cook, pop the @brioche buns{2} onto a baking tray.

Warm in the oven, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye on them so they don't burn!

To assemble the burgers, spread a spoonful of @aioli{1%sachet} over each base
bun.

Top with the cheesy beef burger and buttered leeks.

Close with the top bun.

Serve with chips alongside.